llm_analysis.remediation_advice:
Replace the string concatenation at line 47 with a parameterized query, e.g.:
  String sql = "SELECT userid from USERS where USERNAME=’foo’ and PASSWORD=?";
  Long results = org.owasp.benchmark.helpers.DatabaseHelper.JDBCtemplate.queryForObject(sql, new Object[]{param});
Or use PreparedStatement to avoid injection.

Replace the string concatenation at line 47 with a parameterized query, e.g.:
```java
String sql = "INSERT INTO users (username, password) VALUES (?, ?)";
java.sql.PreparedStatement stmt = org.owasp.benchmark.helpers.DatabaseHelper.getSqlStatement();
stmt.setString(1, "foo");
stmt.setString(2, param);
int count = stmt.executeUpdate();
```
This will eliminate the SQL injection risk and improve performance by reusing the same SQL statement.

